Anitha Kumari

Journey Mapping Study for a Prominent Healthcare App

Healthgrade, a leading online healthcare platform, allows people to find and book in-person or telemedicine appointments for medical or dental care.

Healthgarde realises the importance of Usability in Telehealth Applications, and as the userbase expands it has become increasingly important to address user diversity and inclusivity

Project Focus

The study is part of an outreach program by Healthgrade. With an active user base of 100 mln users, Healthgrade is currently viewed purely as a destination for Primary Care doctors; the app now wants to invite new user groups

Some key questions this research study aims to answer:

  1. Understanding the user journey to choosing a doctor for long term ailments.

  2. Get indepth understanding of the functional and emotional needs across stages

  3. Coming up with user relevant metrics to be integrated in the app and the website

UX Research Methods

Customer Journey Map

TESTING RESULTS

Key Learnings

  1. Trust is a crucial factor, considering there are Moments of high Emotional Volatility through the Consumer Journey

  2. There are several influencers along the patients’ journey, including friends, family, peers who experienced the same ailment before them

  3. Patients care greatly about ‘speed to care’ and want early appointments. The current waiting time for most doctors on the app was >27 days

Design Recommendations

Add Contextual Cues- Prompts in the search tab on the patients condition

Scope for early entry into the into the patient journey, at the 'Research Stage' by providing information/ articles on the condition on the App

Adding case studies to the doctor’s profile will help build Trust and Confidence

“Back” button to be redone such that it actually does take you back one step instead of taking you straight back to the main screen

Implementation

Added search by Symptom feature

Onboarding of Doctors with lower wait times

Work led to considering ‘booking appointments’ on the app

Increased nudges to patients to provide Testimonials, Ratings
